OOC: No problem.  It gave me the chance to make things interresting. 
Remember Tucson&#39;s weakness?  Well, part of that is starting to surface. 
He&#39;s lost his temper and Straight Shot picked up on it. But to cover 
himself, he told her it was a pure bluff.  So it looks like he&#39;s bluffing to 
try to fool the enemy, or is it really a bluff? Did he mean everything he 
said, and did he also intend to ram his foot into Megatron&#39;s fallen body? 
This is a great chance for Rodimus to over come his self doubt as his own 
comrade&#39;s emotional stability seems to be wearing thin.  And now, he 
threatens to put an arrow straight through the chest of the fallen 
Decepticon leader, if the enemy does not stand down.  You could call this a 
fit of bottled up rage that he&#39;s had for a long time, since his own 
unfortunate incident when he was shot down and taken off line, only to fail 
in his mission to protect his comrades.  He doesn&#39;t take failure very well 
since that, and he&#39;ll do everything in his power to make sure it doesn&#39;t 
happen again.

Straight Shot doesn&#39;t know the full scope of Tucson&#39;s issues, it may be up 
to Rodimus to fill in the gaps for her.

As far as what happened, it was the day that Rodimus had been taken by 
Hydras, as Tucson desperately tried to fend off the enemy, by providing a 
decoy to get the enemy to focus on him rather than Rodimus.  He was taken 
off line by Cyclonus long before he could actually accomplish what he was 
trying to do, and the only one who saw that shot, was Straight Shot, who 
just shortly after that, was taken off line herself.  Tucson was in vehicle 
mode when it happened, and can not remember anything of that battle due to 
the cranial shot he endured.  This is what makes him so angry.  The fact 
that he feels that he failed Rodimus and the others the first time, and now 
he&#39;s in danger of failing them again.  You could say that even though he may 
think he doesn&#39;t need help, he could really use Rodimus&#39;s support right 
about now.

